\mathrm{cl}(3)
x \in \mathbb{R}^*
x \sim 3
3 \sim x
 \begin{align*}   \mathrm{cl}(3) &   = \{ x \in \mathbb{R}^* : x/3 \in H \}   = \{ x \in \mathbb{R}^* : \exists m \in \mathbb{Z}, x/3 = 2^m \} \\   &= \{ x \in \mathbb{R}^* : \exists m \in \mathbb{Z}, x = 3 \cdot 2^m \}   = \{ 3 \cdot 2^m : m \in \mathbb{Z} \} \end{align*} 
